	<p>THE PLATFORM FOR THE ARTISTIC COMMUNITY
	Panóplia is a platform that connects artists from different backgrounds to professional opportunities in their art. It is the ideal place for companies to find the right person that matches its creative needs – be them musical, aesthetical or performative.
	</p>
	<br/>
	<p>
	FOR THE EMPOWERMENT OF ARTISTS
	Panóplia is on a mission to gather artists from every sector into a single platform, to provide better chances for professional success. 
	We want painters, musicians, illustrators, actors and actresses, sculptors and sculptresses, designers and every other kind of artist you can think of to join us, so we can find them jobs, freelance opportunities, contests and other initiatives where they can practice their arts.
	</p>
	<br/>
	<p>
	HOW WAS PANÓPLIA BORN?
	In 2019, six university seniors organized an arts exhibition for their bachelor’s degree’s final project. 
	What was to be an ordinary exhibition soon turns into a diverse cultural event, with live tattooing, live music and talks with distinguished guests about the arts sector.
	That spring day at Anjos70 was a success and it inspired Panóplia to plan its next edition in 2020. But Covid-19 invaded our lives. It was impossible to plan an event - Panóplia had to reinvent itself.
	And so it was. We focused on finding new ways of empowering artists using online tools. Against all circumstances, we enabled new opportunities for the cultural scenario. 
	The idea came up of creating an online platform to connect artists to professional opportunities in their field. We didn’t hesitate. We fight for a world where being an artist is as possible and rightful as being a doctor, a journalist or an engineer, and not a bit less valued. We continue to work with that goal, everyday.
